"title": "9311: resurrection, of Jesus Christ",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "9311",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The resurrection of Jesus Christ is of central importance to the NT. It affirms the divinity of Jesus Christ, marks the words and deeds of his ministry with God's seal of approval and opens the way to the future resurrection of believers.</p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's resurrection was foreshadowed in the OT</h2>\n<p>In Abraham and Isaac:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen22:5\">GEN 22:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:19\">HEB 11:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah1:17\">JON 1:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah2:10\">JON 2:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:40\">MAT 12:40</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's resurrection was predicted</h2>\n<h3>In the OT</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:3-1Cor15:4\">1CO 15:3–15:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:11\">ISA 53:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos6:2\">HOS 6:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:45-Luke24:46\">LUK 24:45–24:46</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:25-Acts2:31\">ACT 2:25–2:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:35\">ACT 13:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps16:8-Ps16:11\">PSA 16:8–16:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:34\">ACT 13:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:22-Acts26:23\">ACT 26:22–26:23</a></p>\n<h3>By Jesus Christ himself</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:21\">MAT 16:21</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:31\">MRK 8:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:22\">LUK 9:22</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:9\">MAT 17:9</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:9\">MRK 9:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:18-Matt20:19\">MAT 20:18–20:19</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:32-Mark10:34\">MRK 10:32–10:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:31-Luke18:33\">LUK 18:31–18:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:32\">MAT 26:32</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:28\">MRK 14:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:19-John2:21\">JHN 2:19–2:21</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's resurrection was anticipated by the raising of the dead</h2>\n<h3>In the OT</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:35\">HEB 11:35</a></strong> <em>None of the OT or NT miracles are true resurrections. Those raised resumed life as before, their bodies unchanged. Resurrection for Jesus Christ and therefore for his people means a changed body and permanent life in glory. This is the “better resurrection”.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs17:22\">1KI 17:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs4:35\">2KI 4:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs13:21\">2KI 13:21</a></p>\n<h3>In the miracles of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:22\">LUK 7:22</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:4-Matt11:5\">MAT 11:4–11:5</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:23-Matt9:25\">MAT 9:23–9:25</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:38-Mark5:42\">MRK 5:38–5:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:52-Matt27:53\">MAT 27:52–27:53</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:14-Luke7:15\">LUK 7:14–7:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:43-John11:44\">JHN 11:43–11:44</a></p>\n<h2>The sequence of events in Jesus Christ's resurrection</h2>\n<h3>It was preceded by suffering and death</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:8-Phil2:9\">PHP 2:8–2:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:28-John19:33\">JHN 19:28–19:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:9\">HEB 2:9</a></p>\n<h3>It took place on the first day of the week</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:1-John20:2\">JHN 20:1–20:2</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:1-Matt28:2\">MAT 28:1–28:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:2-Mark16:4\">MRK 16:2–16:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:1-Luke24:3\">LUK 24:1–24:3</a></p>\n<h3>It was announced by angels</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:5-Matt28:6\">MAT 28:5–28:6</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:5-Mark16:6\">MRK 16:5–16:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:4-Luke24:6\">LUK 24:4–24:6</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:23\">LUK 24:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:16\">1TI 3:16</a></p>\n<h3>The disciples were reluctant to believe it</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:25-Luke24:26\">LUK 24:25–24:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:13-Mark16:14\">MRK 16:13–16:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:11\">LUK 24:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:24-John20:25\">JHN 20:24–20:25</a></p>\n<h3>The disciples saw the evidence and were ultimately convinced</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:22\">JHN 2:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:33-Luke24:35\">LUK 24:33–24:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:8\">JHN 20:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:18\">JHN 20:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:26-John20:28\">JHN 20:26–20:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:32\">ACT 2:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:15\">ACT 3:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:33\">ACT 4:33</a></p>\n<h3>The risen Christ appeared to many people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:3\">ACT 1:3</a></strong> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:16-Matt28:17\">MAT 28:16–28:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:14\">MRK 16:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:50-Luke24:52\">LUK 24:50–24:52</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:19-John20:23\">JHN 20:19–20:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:26-John20:31\">JHN 20:26–20:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John21:1-John21:2\">JHN 21:1–21:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:9-Acts1:11\">ACT 1:9–1:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:9\">MRK 16:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:11-John20:18\">JHN 20:11–20:18</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:13-Luke24:15\">LUK 24:13–24:15</a> <em>to two on the Emmaus road</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:34\">LUK 24:34</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:5\">1CO 15:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:3-Acts9:5\">ACT 9:3–9:5</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts22:6-Acts22:8\">ACT 22:6–22:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:12-Acts26:15\">ACT 26:12–26:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:8\">1CO 15:8</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:39-Acts10:41\">ACT 10:39–10:41</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:6\">1CO 15:6</a> <em>to over 500 people</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:7\">1CO 15:7</a> <em>to James</em></p>\n<h3>The resurrection was followed by Jesus Christ's entry into glory</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:34\">ROM 8:34</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:24-1Cor15:29\">1CO 15:24–15:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:18-Eph1:21\">EPH 1:18–1:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:16\">1TI 3:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:3\">HEB 1:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:18\">REV 1:18</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's resurrection body was spiritual but not ghostly</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:37-Luke24:39\">LUK 24:37–24:39</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:27\">JHN 20:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:4\">ACT 1:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:50\">1CO 15:50</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:21\">PHP 3:21</a></p>",
